commit.message: Updated Readme.
Rename animals questions file to be consistent with the rest.
Remove usage of English in German prompts file.
Fixed a JSON format error in de/GENERAL questions file.
Change the handling of stop command to exit the game immediately.

Major refactor to remove the nesting under lambda/custom and bring
all the source code into /src directory.
Removed some dead code.
Update the package.json file
Updated the model files for all regions.
Added German questions for german customers.
Fix a bug. We need to check ER status code, not status.
Handle the case when an unsupported category is requested by the user.

Move away from requestAttributes translation function to interactions
module.
Sorting questions into the right categories and deleting some questions that are too long, too difficult etc.
Rename some translation files in en to be consistent with de

Adjust the localizationClient language based on the request so we don't
keep returning the questions in the same language for customers from
different locales.
Fix all German prompts. Relying on Google translator for now.
Added sustainability questions in English.

Change the language of the translator so we use the right language
for the right customer.

Made several modifications to reliably support a second language (German
was tested).

Instead of using raw slot values for game_category, we start using the
entity resolved value and its identifier. This removes the language from
the equation making it possible to support multiple languages.

Adjust the categories to reflect the new categories being
supported and delete the old categories like movies which
won't be supported at launch time.

A major rearchitecture that touches several files. Unfortunately,
this commit doesn't address a single issue but fixes several bugs,
extracts functions into separate files, fixes questions data files etc.

Introduced categories by language and integrated with i18next
to obtain the right categories for the right languages.
Add a file with instructions on how to extract trivia questions.
Added more trivia questions into the general and animals categories.

Added 2054 technology questions. The questions are the same as the
questions for the science category.

I need to filter the science/technology questions so the right questions
are in the right category. For now, science and technology categories
are a uniion of science and technology questions.

Added 2054 science questions.
Source for the questions - https://raw.githubusercontent.com/uberspot/OpenTriviaQA/master/categories/science-technology

true/false, yes/no questions were discarded.
Added icon files.
First cut of using Dialog to elicit game category slot.

Pulled prompts localization logic into its own module so
the function need not be added to the request attributes
and shuttled back and forth between Alexa cloud and the skill
lambda.

In the new logic, the localization client and the strings stay
in the lambda. This should hopefully make the skill faster because
we aren't shuttling those strings back and forth within the request
attributes.
